        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 5:21AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 521 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles east of Brevard to 19 miles northwest
of Pickens to 10 miles east of Franklin. Movement was southeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Toxaway, Pumpkintown, Graveyard Fields, Tigerville, Wolf
Mountain, Jocassee Gorges, Looking Glass, Cleveland, Devils Fork
State Park, and Sapphire.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until noon EDT for
western North Carolina...and Upstate South Carolina.</instruction>
